
SNS

1) What is SNS ?
Ans:-Simple  notification Service is like central messaging system on aws.
SNS supports various ways of delivering messages, such as emails, text messages.

(2) Why do we use SNS ?
Ans:- We use SNS because its like a helpful messenger for our computer systems. This makes
           our sysytems more flexible and able to handle a lot messages.

(3) What is an Amazon SNS function, and how we can configure it.
Ans:-Amazon SNS is like messaging hub.
*Topics
*Messages
*Subscribes
*Delivery Methods
*filters

(4) Difference between Amazon SNS & Amazon SQS.
Ans:- Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service):
 Job: Sends quick, real-time messages or notifications.
 Imagine: Broadcasting a message to a group chat.
Amazon SQS (Simple Queue Service):
 Job: Manages a queue of messages for orderly processing.
 Imagine: Putting tasks in a to-do list and someone else takes tasks from the list.

(5)What are the different delivery formats and transports in AWS SNS ?
Ans:- * HTTP/HTTPS
* Email/Email-JSON
*Amazon SQS
* AWS lambda
*SMS
*Application
(6) What is the difference between SNS FIFO & Standard while creating the SNS topic.
Ans:- SNS topic:- messages are quaranteed to arrive in the order they were sent.
            SNS fifo:- messages might not arrive in exact order they were sent.

(7) On which services are configured with the AWS SNS ?
Ans:-*SQS
*AWS lambda
*Amazon S3
*Amazon EC2
*AWS cloudwatch
*Amazon RDS

