(9) What are FIFO topics on SNS ?
Ans:-* message order
* no duplicates
* use cases
* not for high throughput
 
(9) What is SNS Mobile Push ?
Ans:- SNS refers to the capability of SNS to send push notification to mobile devices.
        this feature is commonly used by mobile app developers to keep users informed about    updates 

(10) On which delivery method do we use and configure the subscription ?
Ans:- When configuring subscription in amazon SNS choose the dekivery method based on how you want to receive the notifications.
*HTTP/HTTPS endpoints
*Email/Email-JSON endpoints
*Amazon SQS
*AWS lambda endpoints
*mobile push endpoints
*application endpoints

AWS EC2

(1) What is EC2, Why do we need EC2 service in cloud computing ?
Ans:-EC2 is like a computer rental service in the cloud. We can use these virtual computers for various tasks like running websites, processig data.
*flexibilty
*cost efficiency
*various jobs
*easy scaling
*global reach
*no physical maintainance
 
(2) Features of Amazon EC2 ?
Ans:-*scalabilty
*variety of instances
*pricing models
* customizable virtual machines
* security groups and virtual private cloud
* amazon machine images

(3) What is Hypervisor ? and its types ?
Ans:- A hypervisor also known as a virtual machine monitor. Its smart tool that helps your computer do multiple jobs at once.
Types:-
Type1:- is generally more secure and stable because it does not run on top of another O/S.
Type2:- are easier to install configure and use than bare metal hypervisor.

(4) Where we use hypervisor ?
Ans:-* Computers centers
* internet cloud services
*school labs and online learning
 
(5) Steps to create an EC2 instance?
Ans:-* EC2 service
*launch instance
*choose AMI
*choose instance type
*configure instance
*add storage
*security group
*review and launch
*create key pair
*launch instance
*connect to instance 

(6) EC2 Instance state ?
Ans:-* pending
*running
*stopping
*stopped
*terminating
*terminated

(7) How many types of EC2 Instance-State codes ?
Ans:-*pending(code:0)
*running(code:16)
*shutting down(code:32)
*terminated(code:48)
*stopping(code:64)
*stopped(code:80)

(8) What is the meaning of server hibernating mode ?
Ans:- It is also known as Stopped state, its like turning off your computer but keeping all your files and settings.

 (9) What is KMS ?
Ans:-KMS stands for Key Management Service. KMS hepls you manage encryption keys which are like digital locks used to secure your data.

(10) AWS Amazon EC2 Instance types ?
Ans:-*general purpose instance
*compute optimized instance
*memory optimized
*storage optimized instance
*accelerated computing instance

(11) How many types of status checks happen in aws ?
Ans:-1: System Status Check: makes sure the computers hardware and network are in good shape.
2: Instance Status Checks: makes sure your virtual computer software and connection to the internet are working.

