(14) What are EBS Volumes and its types ?
Ans:-EBS volumes as virtual hard drives that you can attach to your virtual servers on Amazon cloud.
Types:-
* General purpose
*provisional SSD
*Throughout optimized
*cold HDD
* magnetic

(15) Purpose of Using EBS volumes ?
Ans:-*data persistance
*scalable storage
*high performance
*snapshot backups
*data encryption
*attachment to multiple instance

(16) How many types of purchasing options do we have in aws ec2 ?
Ans:-* on –demand instance
	* reserved instance
	* spot instance
	*dedicated hosts
	*dedicated instances
	
(17) Difference between AWS AMI Image & AWS Template ?
Ans;-AWS AMI:- its like taking a picture of your fully set up computer
    AWS Template:- its like having a recipe a build a kitchen with all the appliance specifying how  things should be set up.

(18) What is NIC & it’s types ?
Ans:- NIC means Network Interface Card is hardware component that allows computers to connect to a network.
*Types:- 
*Ethernet NIC
*Wireless NIC
*Fiber NIC
* Bluetooth NIC
*Token Ring NIC
*Modem NIC

(19) What is elastic IP ? & WHY were we used ?
Ans:- An Elastic IP address is a static Ipv4 address designed for dynamic cloud computing.
*Consistent address
*avoiding changes
*easy for security

(20) What is the snapshot of why we use it ?
Ans:- Snapshot is like taking a picture of your computers data at a specific moment.We use snapshots in cloud services like AWS.
*Backup And Recovery
*Data protection
*Cost Efficiency

(21) How can we save money in snapshot costing, if an automated snapshot has been created ?
Ans:- * retention policies
*scheduled snapshots
*snapshots size
*unused snapshots
*data lifecycle management
*automated cleanup
*cost monitoring

(22) What is the lifecycle manager in snapshot ?
Ans:- snapshot lifecycle manager is like a helpful assistant for handling data snapshots.

(23) How does the Amazon lifecycle manager work ?
Ans:- is like helper for managing your data backups on AWS.
*It takes care of backup timing
*Cleaning up old backups

(24) Difference between Security Group & NACL ?
Ans:- Security group:- it decides who can come in and who can go out.
NACL:- it decides who is allowed to enter or leave the entire ared not just on once.

(25) What are NACL & Its types ?
Ans:- Network Access Control List. its a set of rules that control traffic at the subnet level, 
      determining who can come in and who can leave.
